Genetically engineered Marines travel throughout Space, battling depraved heretics, dishonourable traitors, and vile aliens.

This set includes 4 powered gauntlets, two holding the torn off heads of two different types of alien beast - a brutal ork, and a sinister soulstealer. The third holds a retro style space beaky helmet, and the fourth is empty, perhaps for you to add in your own head model! All four have supported versions.

This is an updated version of the first thing I ever tried to 'sculpt', as opposed to arrange geometric shapes - an ork head. It's a little reflection on my part, comparing where I started to where I am. It's been a slow process, as I take what digital hobby time I can in between physical modelling and all my other fickle interests! But it's still nice to see what I feel in some improvement.

You can see the original here:
https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/power-gauntlet-prime-scale-powered-gauntlet-holding-head

I am an amateur enthusiast 3D designer, and appreciate all constructive feedback. Please check out my other designs for more wargame models, and please consider following me, posting a make, or even leaving a donation via my profile!

The battlefields of the grim-dark future are scattered will the everyday materiel of the industrial and military complex required to process war on a galactic scale.

This set offers a sample of a cargo crate, cargo hauler, blank trailer, and pallet of materiel.

These could be printed at 200% for 15mm gaming terrain, or, if you are ambitious, 400% for 28-32mm scale gaming. The models are sufficiently detailed to be printed at larger scale, yet simple and robust enough to print at their intended 6-8mm scale.

This set contains 4 STLs; a sample of the full set, available here:
https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/epic-cargo-road-train-scatter-terrain-6mm-8mm-scale

The full set allows you to customise your selection. It can be used to create cargo 'road trains', linking multiple trailers and cargo containers to create thematic barriers for your miniatures to take cover behind, or individual pieces to add character to the bases of larger miniatures.

They would also make suitable 'toys' what could be added to 28-32mm scale models, adding a layer of horror and inhumanity to the devastation surrounding your grim-dark characters.

The crane and defence trailer is compatible with my other Epic tank turrets, so can be replaced with any of the turrets in this collection:
https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/8mm-scale-grim-dark-tank-turrets-of-russ-nedius

For a variety of projects I've got on, I needed a set of human heads to add to models I intend to sculpt for 3D printing. I couldn't find any I like, so have made up a collection of heads I've created by scratch sculpting, using Blender Add-ons, etc. None are 'stock' generation. The Wastes are home to all manner of terrible creatures, mutated from what were once the humble creatures of the forests. Whether this was by design, genetic mutation, or simply through exposure to chaotic magics is unknown.

This is a collection of mutated beasts, designed for Fantasy and Post-Apocalyptic Wargaming and RPGs. They are truly massive beasts, and so are provided both whole, in kit form, and with hollowed out versions to allow you to chose the right set for your needs. These were made whilst making my toad-dragon (link below), as each time I looked at it, it made me think of a different animal! I saw a rat, molerat, and hippo, and here they are!

I love settings in post apocalyptic fallout shelters, where desert mole rats have mutated into massive beasts, so have a particular fondness for the mole-rat monster here - perfect for creating a monstrous mount for your post apocalyptic raiders or travelling merchants!

The Toad Dragon can be found here:
https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/chaos-toad-dragon

These models come without rider or saddle, and are designed to be kit-bashed with your favourite fantasy range. These parts are also compatible with the bits from the Toad Dragon, and so would complement it nicely.

This is a set of 33 STLs that can act as a base for 2D+ RPG and boardgames set in space / industrial settings.

It's a base for further modelling and creative work. My plan is to use these as a base to add more detailed parts gathered from my bitz box and things I can print in resin. The FDM printed board tiles will provide a robust base to add the finer detailed parts onto. This is part of a personal modelling project to create a more generic space-corridor themed 2d+ tileset I can use with a range of models to play games like Space Hulk, Aliens, Necromunda, things like that. 

Each tile is based around a 32mmx32mm grid, so the larger bases common on 32mm miniatures will fit into the space. Square shaped floor tiles, cut or printed between 30mm - 32mm square will then fit the floor tiles to create a grid on which to play.

Compatible with my Atmosphere Processor Floor tiles set!
https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/atmosphere-processor-rpg-tiles-for-gameboards-bases-and-dioramas


Each board tile features magnet holes for 5x2mm round magnets. However, also provided are two little exta bits - a 'peg' than can be used in place of magnets, and a 1x5mm disc for 'filling' the magnet holes so 5x1mm magnets can be used. When installing pegs, mount them in the lefthand hole only when facing you for each joint. You can do the right hand either, BUT the peg must be in the same side when facing you for every joint.

Included are two example 30x30mm floor tiles. These can be scaled to suit your preference, but will work at that size, or increased to 31mm or 32mm squared. Also included is an example greeble than can be added to the 'walls', to add a little visual interest.

There will be more complex versions of this set coming, with guide holes for floor tiles, mountings for wall decorations, a range of greebles. This will let me make a long time desired hobby project of an 'Aliens' themed Space Hulk board, so I can play a mix of those two games together!..

Please see my other designs for a variety of other sci-fi and fantasy models.

This cobbled-together flying piece of scrap metal looks as if it should fall apart under a gentle breeze. And yet, it barrels through the air with wild abandon; bullets, bombs and stranger projectiles flying from it in all directions. A mighty flying fortress, this super-scrap bomber all but ignores incoming fire as it passes harmlessly through open superstructure, or as it blasts away rusty plating that was all but falling off anyway, leaving critical structures safe below layers of bolted on scrap metal.

This 67 piece multi-part kit comes with a huge range of options. It can be built with two wing profiles, alternative hulls with differing tailfins, and a range of options for turrets and bombs, many of which can be mirrored for additional variety / symmetry. It includes monstrous 'bouncing bombs' for some truly 'wild' bombing runs!

The kit is designed to be scaled to 8mm scale model games, such as plane warfare games, or those featuring legions of models fighting. It could also be used in 6mm games where Epic Marines fight in Space, a real armageddon level battle. Compatable with ork style armies, it would be a great proxy for a mega bommber or landa. It is sufficiently detailed that an ambitious hobbyist could print it at 400% scale to create a huge center piece model or terrain for 32mm games set in grim dark universes. This would of course require additional cuts to the model!

I am a hobbyist 3D modeller - not a professional 3D designed. However, this project has taken many, many hours of development, test printing and correction. It is my first 'paid for' model, a reflection of the time it took to create. Almost all my other models are currently available for free, so please do look through those if you are interested in further supporting me and my hobby.

I also welcome feedback and will look to develop this model with improvments and additional options in future.
